{
  "rationale": "The supervisor prioritizes safety by preventing forward movement in the presence of obstacles, employs systematic wall-following to encourage full coverage, and uses helper states to avoid oscillation and deadlock near corners. Each state reacts deterministically to uncontrollable events, and transitions promote either rotation or backward movement to escape blocked situations.",
  "new_states": [
